---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="Evolution of Cooperation and Fairness" description="How cooperative behaviors evolve in agent-based models." />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      .back { font-size: 13px; color: #888; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
      .back:hover { color: #111; }
      .proj-tag { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; padding: 3px 9px; border-radius: 20px; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.3px; text-transform: uppercase; background: #e1f5ee; color: #0f6e56; }
      h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: -0.3px; line-height: 1.3; }
      .lead { font-size: 1rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.75; max-width: 620px; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; padding-bottom: 2rem; }
      .section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
      .section h2 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #111; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
      .subproj-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
      .subproj { border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem; text-decoration: none; display: block; transition: border-color 0.15s; background: #fafafa; }
      .subproj:hover { border-color: #1d9e75; background: #fff; }
      .subproj h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; color: #111; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .subproj p { font-size: 0.83rem; color: #666; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
      .subproj-arrow { float: right; color: #aaa; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 2px; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <a href="/projects" class="back">← Back to projects</a>
      <span class="proj-tag">Biology · Game theory</span>
      <h1>Evolution of cooperation and fairness</h1>
      <p class="lead">How and why do cooperative behaviors evolve when selfish strategies seem to dominate? This research area uses agent-based models and evolutionary game theory to understand the mechanisms that sustain cooperation across different scales and contexts.</p>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Projects in this area</h2>
        <div class="subproj-list">

          <a href="/projects/coop-ibi" class="subproj">
            <span class="subproj-arrow">→</span>
            <h3>Co-evolution of inter-birth interval and sharing behaviors</h3>
            <p>Explores how birth spacing and resource-sharing behaviors co-evolve in agent populations.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="/projects/coop-large-scale" class="subproj">
            <span class="subproj-arrow">→</span>
            <h3>Large scale cooperation</h3>
            <p>Investigates the mechanisms that allow cooperation to scale beyond small kin groups to large anonymous societies.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="/projects/coop-partner" class="subproj">
            <span class="subproj-arrow">→</span>
            <h3>Partner choice in cooperation</h3>
            <p>Studies how selective partner choice shapes the evolution of cooperative behavior and reputation systems.</p>
          </a>

        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
